I wouldn't stick with 2HB either, but he said h2h. :)

I would try to keep your h2h maxed or near maxed and mix in some 1hb, piercing and 2hb when possible. It is good to keep your options open and not have to try to catch up later. You can probably find some nice 1hb weapons a lot cheaper than nice h2h weapons.

The best thing to do is look around in the bazaar for some cheap stuff you can use.  As a barbarian, collect some spiderling silk and bear/wolf pelts in Everfrost to sell and use the cash to upgrade.

I would suggest getting a Polished Steel Ulak (PSU) as your h2h weapon to start. Maybe even get two of them when you can dual wield.

My 26 Beastlord has been concentrating on h2h and 1hb with a smattering of piercing.  I plan to get all my skills up at some point though.

Good luck.

